subs.text: July 11

Just pushed out a minor update to the @Neo_Blockchain tookit. Neo-Express v3.3.27 enables the new RpcServer Traverse Iterators feature by default. This feature enables JSON-RPC clients to fully enumerate iterators returned from contract operations [link]
subs.rawText:
Just pushed out a minor update to the @Neo_Blockchain  tookit.

Neo-Express v3.3.27 enables the new RpcServer Traverse Iterators feature by default. This feature enables JSON-RPC clients to fully enumerate iterators returned from contract operations

https://t.co/6UDf855SUv

subs.text: If you want to see Traverse Iterators in action, the Neo Contributor NFT sample client application has been updated to use them to enumerate the available NFTs. [link]
subs.rawText:
If you want to see Traverse Iterators in action, the Neo Contributor NFT sample client application has been updated to use them to enumerate the available NFTs.

https://t.co/PFB3vo9awu

subs.text: Neo-Express 3.3.27 also fixes a couple of issues with command line processing for the new contract download command. These fixes make contract download a little easier to execute and makes the argument usage consistent between direct and batch mode.
subs.rawText: Neo-Express 3.3.27 also fixes a couple of issues with command line processing for the new contract download command. These fixes make contract download a little easier to execute and makes the argument usage consistent between direct and batch mode.

subs.text: July 6
We just shipped the latest #NeoBlockchainToolkit for @Neo_Blockchain v3.3.1 last week. Unfortunately, we had to update the Neo.BuildTasks package to address a Neo C# compiler issue. [link]
subs.rawText:
We just shipped the latest #NeoBlockchainToolkit for @Neo_Blockchain v3.3.1 last week. Unfortunately, we had to update the Neo.BuildTasks package to address a Neo C# compiler issue.

https://t.co/Od0nMhPy2L

subs.text: Neo.BuildTasks v3.3.23 addresses the issue, fixes a couple bugs, adds new tests and adds a new ContractNameOverride attribute to give developers more control over the generated test code. [link]
subs.rawText:
Neo.BuildTasks v3.3.23 addresses the issue, fixes a couple bugs, adds new tests and adds a new ContractNameOverride attribute to give developers more control over the generated test code.

https://t.co/maszyFKvJ3

subs.text: There's also a new doc that describes the various MSBuild properties and items that Neo.BuildTasks uses and provides guidance for upgrading your v3.1 project to v3.3 (mostly removing stuff that's no longer needed) [link]
subs.rawText:
There's also a new doc that describes the various MSBuild properties and items that Neo.BuildTasks uses and provides guidance for upgrading your v3.1 project to v3.3 (mostly removing stuff that's no longer needed)

https://t.co/5WrvYbypLS
